Introduction

EVNNE is a 7-member boy group under Jellyfish Entertainment. They debuted on September 19th of 2023 with the mini-album “Target: Me”. The name of their group is an acronym for "EVENing's Newest Etoiles".

The group consists of seven talented trainees who were previously contestants on the survival show Boys Planet. They are Park Hanbin, Lee Jeonghyeon, Mun Junghyun, and Park Jihoo from WAKEONE; Yoo Seungeon and Ji Yunseo from Yue Hua Entertainment; and Keita from Rain Company and Ciipher.

The group formerly went with the name "BLIT" an acronym for "Boldly Leaping Into Tomorrow" but was changed after fans raised concerns of misinterpretation.
